<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2809] Setting certain nested javac arguments in groovyc leads to an exception.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2809</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;ant = new AntBuilder()
ant.taskdef(name: &apos;groovyc&apos;, classname: &apos;org.codehaus.groovy.ant.Groovyc&apos;)
ant.delete(dir: &quot;classes&quot;)
ant.mkdir(dir: &quot;classes&quot;)
ant.groovyc(srcDir: &apos;src&apos;, destDir: &apos;classes&apos;) {
    javac(source: &quot;1.4&quot;, target: &quot;1.4&quot;, nowarn: &apos;on&apos;)
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It does not matter whether I set nowarn to true, &apos;true&apos;, or &apos;on&apos;. I get the exception in any case. The same happens for verbose and depend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;  [groovyc] org.codehaus.groovy.control.MultipleCompilationErrorsException: startup failed, Invalid commandline usage for javac.
  [groovyc] javac: invalid flag: -nowarnon
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

</description>
